            <h2 class="section-title">About Me</h2>
            
            <div class="about-content">
                <div>
                    <h3>Ian Omara Otiato</h3>
                    <p>I am a recent graduate from Pioneer International University with a degree in International Relations and Diplomacy, having specialized in Peace and Security.</p>
                    
                    <p>My journey into software engineering might seem unconventional, but I've discovered that the problem-solving skills and systems thinking required in International Relations translate remarkably well to coding. Just as diplomacy requires understanding complex systems and finding creative solutions to global challenges, software engineering involves understanding complex systems and creating elegant solutions to technical problems.</p>
                    
                    <div class="certification">
                        <h4><i class="fab fa-wordpress-simple"></i> WordPress Certification</h4>
                        <p>I have successfully completed the THIRD WordPress certification program, enhancing my skills in web development and content management systems.</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <p>My inspiration for creating this platform came from personal experience. I witnessed my grandfather's struggle with throat cancer and saw firsthand how it affected not just his physical health, but his mental wellbeing too. This experience made me realize the critical connection between physical health and mental wellness, especially for men who often hesitate to seek help or discuss their health concerns.</p>
                    
                    <p>This project combines my passion for creating positive change with my growing technical skills. I believe that technology can be a powerful tool for health advocacy and education, particularly in reaching communities that might not have easy access to traditional health resources.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="about-img">
